<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <p><span class="Emphasis"><MadCap:variable name="cc_product_vars.CV-full" /> scan</span>:  Whereas <span class="Emphasis"><MadCap:variable name="cc_product_vars.CV-full" /> discovery</span> scans the workspace to <span class="Emphasis">discover the structure</span> of the workspace, the <span class="Emphasis"><MadCap:variable name="cc_product_vars.CV-full" /> scan</span> scans the workspace for <span class="Emphasis">informational updates for the purpose of identity and entitlement analysis</span>.</p>
        <p>You have to trigger <span class="Emphasis"><MadCap:variable name="cc_product_vars.CV-full" /> scans</span> manually from the relevant workspace page in <MadCap:variable name="cc_product_vars.CV-full" /> (<span class="Emphasis">Settings &gt; Platform management</span>). For more information, see <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="cc_product_conds.CV"><MadCap:xref href="../cv-connect-workspaces.htm">Connect and manage workspaces</MadCap:xref></MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="cc_product_conds.SCA">the <a href="/cloud-visibility/latest/en/content/cloudadmin/cv-connect-workspaces.htm"><MadCap:variable name="cc_product_vars.CV-full" /> docs</a></MadCap:conditionalText>.</p>
        <div class="note">
            <p>To perform a <span class="Emphasis"><MadCap:variable name="cc_product_vars.CV-full" /> scan</span>, the workspace must be <span class="Emphasis">onboarded </span> and <MadCap:variable name="cc_product_vars.CV-full" /> must be <span class="Emphasis">connected</span> to the workspace. See <MadCap:xref href="#onboard-vs-connect">onboard vs connect</MadCap:xref> above.</p>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>